Document 1: Manulife Employee Leave Policy
File Name: SOP_HR_Leave_Policy_2026.txt

TITLE: Manulife Global Employee Leave and Time-Off Policy
DEPARTMENT: Human Resources & Operations
EFFECTIVE DATE: January 1, 2026
APPLIES TO: All full-time Manulife and John Hancock employees.

1. Paid Time Off (PTO) Entitlement

All full-time employees are entitled to a minimum of 20 days of Paid Time Off (PTO) per calendar year, accrued bi-weekly.

Employees with over 5 years of tenure receive 25 days of PTO.

Up to 5 unused PTO days can be rolled over to the next calendar year. Any additional unused days will be forfeited unless restricted by local labor laws.

2. Sick and Mental Health Leave

Employees receive 10 days of paid sick leave annually. This can be used for physical illness, mental health days, or caring for an immediate family member.

Absences exceeding 3 consecutive business days require a standard doctor's note to be uploaded to the Manulife Workday HR Portal.

3. Parental Leave

Primary caregivers are eligible for up to 16 weeks of fully paid parental leave following the birth, adoption, or foster placement of a child.

Secondary caregivers are eligible for up to 6 weeks of fully paid parental leave.

4. Request and Approval Process

Standard Requests: PTO requests must be submitted through the Workday HR Portal at least 14 days in advance for approval by the direct manager.

Emergency/Sick Leave: Must be logged in Workday on the same day, and the employee must notify their manager via Microsoft Teams or email before their shift begins.

Document 2: Customer Onboarding Procedure
File Name: SOP_Ops_Customer_Onboarding.txt

TITLE: Customer Onboarding and Account Provisioning SOP
DEPARTMENT: System Operations & Client Success
EFFECTIVE DATE: February 15, 2026
SYSTEMS USED: ClientLink Hub, SecureDoc Portal, Salesforce

1. Initial Verification & KYC (Know Your Customer)

Once a customer signs the initial Manulife policy agreement, the Operations agent must verify the customer's identity.

The agent must log into the ClientLink Hub and ensure the customer's Government ID and Proof of Address match the application details.

If documents are blurry or mismatched, the agent must trigger a "Request for Information" (RFI) via the SecureDoc Portal. Do not process the application until documents are verified.

2. Account Creation & Policy Linking

Navigate to the Salesforce onboarding dashboard.

Create a new "Client Profile" using the verified email address.

Enter the Policy Generation Number (PGN) into the profile to link the customer's specific life insurance or wealth management product to their digital account.

Set the account status to "Active - Pending Welcome Packet."

3. Welcome Packet Dispatch

Once the account is active, the system will automatically generate a Welcome Packet.

The Ops agent must manually review the Welcome Packet for accuracy (Name, Policy Amount, Beneficiary details).

Click "Approve & Send." The customer will receive an encrypted email containing their login credentials and policy documents.

4. Tier 2 Escalations for Onboarding

If the ClientLink Hub throws an "AML Flag" (Anti-Money Laundering), the Ops agent must immediately halt the onboarding process.

The agent must change the Salesforce status to "Escalated - Compliance Review" and assign the ticket to the Regional Compliance Officer. Do not notify the customer of the AML flag directly; inform them only that "the application is under standard secondary review."
